      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAW CHRISTIE (3) was in the minors two back (25.96) at Geelong but ran below best last time at this track, finishing 6th. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. ZIPPING ARVADA (4) ran below her best last time finishing fifth (22.51) over 390m at Ballarat in a Grade 4/5. Has never missed the frame here at the trip from three starts. Better than last start and can bounce back. PAW LASSIE (1) scored well last start as odds-on favourite by 1.5 lengths at this track in a handy 23.66 beating Where's The Gold. Has the coveted inside box and in form and has the ability. Has performed well from this box with a win and three minor placings to her name from four starts. Should be in this for a long way. OCEAN GOLD (2) is likely to have admirers.",
